Numerical results

The total species pool is 431 species, of which 189 (44%) are aliens and 242 are natives.

We study 71 focal species, including 47 aliens ( 66 %).

This is a non random subsample of the total pool of species in terms of alien status (Fisher exact test: odds ratio = 0.4, P = 0.001 )

We found negative critical abundances for 11 aliens and 1 native. This corresponds to a higher proportion of aliens vs.natives given the focal species pool (Fisher exact test: odds ratio = 0.15, P = 0.049 )

Above critical abundances, we lose on average -1.95 (+- 0.81) species in mean alpha richness, and -25.78 (+- 17.15) species in total gamma richness compared to the null model accounting for sample size.
